HEADWORD: Spumy
<hw>Spum"y</hw>
<pr>(sp⟦umac⟧m"⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>spumosus</ets>, fr. <ets>spuma</ets> foam: cf. F.
<ets>spumeux</ets>.]</ety> <def>Consisting of, containing, or covered
with, froth, scum, or foam; frothy; foamy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>spumous</qex> and florid state of the blood.</q>
<rj><qau>Arbuthnot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>spumy</qex> waves proclaim the watery war.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

